                <pb/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Zurich, Switzerland<lb/>April 10th, at night</dateline>
                    <salute>Carson, child my beloved,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>you know that, leaving the day after tomorrow,<lb/>
                    feeling half-afraid and proud, leaving behind<lb/>
                    me all I care for, once again, + a wave of love, --<lb/>
                    yesterday, talking to a really good friend about<lb/>
                    America, -- explaining why I wrote a most critical<lb/>
                    + terribly serious article on Chaplin's "Great Dictator",<lb/>
                    -- explaining, painting the entire profound horror of<lb/>
                    Disney's Fantasia, -- I was quite desperate, but found<lb/>
                    myself in the end breaking out in one enthousiastic feeling<lb/>
                    + belief in the U. S. being not better [...]</p>
                <p>I remembered you manuscript, + felt bitter [...]</p>
                <pb/>
                <p>This was like a symbol [...]</p>
